message:
Running command: python3 - << 'PY'
import os,sys,subprocess
# produce a git diff of working tree changes relative to index/HEAD for all files we edited
files=[
 '/workspace/requests/requests/structures.py',
 '/workspace/requests/requests/cookies.py',
 '/workspace/requests/requests/utils.py',
 '/workspace/requests/requests/models.py',
 '/workspace/requests/requests/sessions.py',
]
# run git diff --no-index between original files in repo (none) and current files? Instead, just show unified diffs from git by reading HEAD and file contents
for f in files:
    try:
        # try to get git blob of HEAD for file
        head = subprocess.check_output(['git','show','HEAD:'+os.path.relpath(f, start='/workspace')], cwd='/workspace', text=True)
    except subprocess.CalledProcessError:
        head = ''
    cur = open(f,'r',encoding='utf-8').read()
    if head!=cur:
        import difflib
        diff=''.join(difflib.unified_diff(head.splitlines(keepends=True), cur.splitlines(keepends=True), fromfile='a'+f, tofile='b'+f))
        sys.stdout.write(diff)
PY
